-- Peru Bank Lending Rose 18 Percent Last Year, Andina Reports
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2012-01-25T22:07:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-25/peru-bank-lending-rose-18-percent-last-year-andina-reports.html
Peru’s outstanding bank loans
climbed 18 percent last year amid rising demand for consumer and
mortgage credit, Andina  reported .  Bank deposits rose 8.9 percent in 2011, the state news
agency said, citing comments by Javier Poggi, head of research
at the country’s financial regulator. Poggi said 45 percent of
outstanding loans and 41 percent of deposits were denominated in
dollars, according to Andina.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
